Fundamentals of the "Jávea Factor" and Operational Schedule

From a real estate perspective, the municipality of Jávea consolidates a trend of resilience and price growth above the average of the Mediterranean coast. The persistent demand for spacious residential spaces combined with proximity to natural and coastal environments has positioned the locality as a priority attraction hub for both domestic primary-residence buyers and high-net-worth individuals and remote workers from the European Union. The location on Calle Arquitecto Urteaga balances proximity to the essential services of the urban core with quick access to the port and beach areas, sustaining the competitiveness of the final product in the open market.

The development's operational schedule keeps its development milestones aligned with the forecasts of the original business plan. After the close of the fundraising campaign was formalized in May 2026, the next technical steps are aimed at obtaining and finalizing the building licence over the coming months. Subsequently, the physical foundation and structural works for the 85 residential units will begin, maintaining the horizon for completion of construction, deed execution and distribution of dividends to the investors of the Limited Company within the time window set for the first half of 2028.

